  ### How to Test the Implementation

  Since the  /api/debug/*  routes sit behind the dashboard's  requireAuth  middleware, you must first obtain a dashboard session JWT.

  #### Step 1: Login / Setup Dashboard Session

  If setting up a fresh local workspace, initialize the admin account:

    curl -X POST http://localhost:3001/api/auth/setup \
      -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
      -d '{"email": "admin@example.com", "password": "supersecretpassword"}'

  Note: If the account is already set up, login instead at  /api/auth/login  using the same JSON payload.
  This returns a JSON containing a  "token"  string. Copy the token.

  #### Step 2: Seed the Media Models Table

  Execute the seed endpoint using your dashboard token:

    curl -X POST http://localhost:3001/api/debug/seed-media \
      -H "Authorization: Bearer <dashboard_jwt_token>"

  • Expected Response (First Run):
    { "success": true, "rowsInserted": 1, "mediaModelsCount": 1, "audioModelsCount": 1 }

  • Expected Response (Subsequent Runs due to idempotency):
    { "success": true, "rowsInserted": 0, "mediaModelsCount": 1, "audioModelsCount": 1 }


  #### Step 3: Check Media Status

  Query the seeded entries:

    curl -X GET http://localhost:3001/api/debug/media-status \
      -H "Authorization: Bearer <dashboard_jwt_token>"

  • Expected Response:
    {
      "totalMediaModels": 1,
      "audioModels": 1,
      "imageModels": 0,
      "transcriptionModels": 0,
      "models": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "platform": "google",
          "model_id": "gemini-2.5-flash-preview-tts",
          "display_name": "Gemini 2.5 Flash TTS",
          "modality": "audio",
          "priority": 1,
          "enabled": 1,
          "quota_label": "Keyless"
        }
      ]
    }


  #### Step 4: Verify Text-to-Speech (TTS)

  Now call the OpenAI-compatible speech endpoint using your unified API token ( freellmapi-... ):

    curl -X POST http://localhost:3001/v1/audio/speech \
      -H "Authorization: Bearer <unified_api_key>" \
      -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
      -d '{
        "model": "gemini-2.5-flash-preview-tts",
        "input": "Hello world"
      }' --output speech.mp3

  • Expected Outcome: The request no longer throws the 503  "No enabled audio providers configured."  error. It successfully retrieves the seeded
  row and proceeds directly to execute the Google TTS adapter.